## ALL 17 MODULES

### PORTFOLIO INTELLIGENCE

MODULE 1 — PORTFOLIO HEALTH MONITOR
The moment you open AEGIS you see one number — your Portfolio Health Score from 0 to 100. Green means your money is working normally. Yellow means there is turbulence worth watching. Red means something significant happened and action may be needed. This score is calculated every 60 seconds using your Sharpe Ratio, sector concentration, CVaR distance, and current sentiment around your held stocks. The complexity runs invisibly. The user sees one clean number and one clear color.

MODULE 2 — ADVISORY ENGINE
AEGIS analyses every stock you own and generates a signal — Buy more, Hold, Watch carefully, or Review your position. Every signal comes with a plain English reason and the specific factors that drove it — price forecast, news sentiment, institutional activity, technical indicators, and your current portfolio balance. AEGIS never says "you must sell." It says "here are three reasons some investors are reducing exposure — and here is the counter-argument for holding." The final decision is always yours.

MODULE 3 — RECOVERY ADVISOR
This is the feature that defines AEGIS. No other retail platform has it. When your portfolio suffers a statistically significant loss — calculated using CVaR, not an arbitrary percentage — the Recovery Engine activates automatically. It identifies which exact market factor caused the loss using SHAP analysis. It then runs 500 simulated recovery scenarios based on 20 years of similar historical events using Monte Carlo simulation. It collapses all 500 simulations into three human-readable recovery paths:

Conservative — slowest, safest, lowest risk, longest timeline
Balanced — optimal risk-adjusted recovery, recommended in most cases
Aggressive — fastest recovery, higher risk, requires available capital

Each path shows specific actions, estimated recovery timeline, and the historical data behind the estimate. The user picks a lane. AEGIS explains it in plain English. They execute it themselves through their broker.

MODULE 4 — EMOTIONAL BIAS TRACKER
AEGIS reads your complete trade history from your Demat account and identifies your personal behavioral patterns. It calculates how many times you panic-sold during dips that later recovered. How many times you bought at peaks out of FOMO. How early you sold your winners. How long you held your losers. It assigns you an Emotional Bias Score and calculates exactly how much each pattern has cost you in rupees. Not a quiz, not a personality test. Your real data. Your real cost. Every time you try to override an AEGIS suggestion, it shows you your history: "You have overridden AEGIS 6 times. It was right 5 of those times. Those 5 decisions cost you ₹12,400." Then it gives you the choice — override anyway, or trust the system.

MODULE 5 — PORTFOLIO X-RAY
Most investors think they are diversified. Most are not. AEGIS proves it with a correlation analysis — showing how much each stock in your portfolio moves together with every other stock. Owning Infosys, TCS, Wipro, and HCL feels like four different investments. They move together 85–90% of the time because they serve the same clients, depend on the same Dollar/Rupee rate, and are affected by the same macro events. Portfolio X-Ray shows your real sector concentration, hidden correlations, and true diversification score. It then suggests which sectors would actually reduce your risk if added.

