### MARKET INTELLIGENCE

MODULE 6 — INTELLIGENCE FEED
A live feed of news and social media signals filtered, scored, and sorted specifically for you. Sources pulled every 60 seconds:

StockTwits — purpose-built financial social network, every post tagged with ticker and sentiment
Twitter/X — verified CEO accounts, Fed officials, major analysts
Reddit — WallStreetBets and investing subreddits for retail sentiment
Telegram — Indian market alert channels, SEBI updates, brokerage research
NewsAPI and Reuters RSS — structured verified financial news
YouTube transcripts — major financial channel sentiment

Every item goes through a bot filter, then FinBERT sentiment scoring, then ticker extraction to match against your portfolio, then impact scoring — HIGH, MEDIUM, or LOW. Mistral-7B writes one plain English summary line for each item. The feed is sorted into three tiers:

Tier 1 — News about stocks you own or AEGIS is watching for you. Always first.
Tier 2 — Market movers. Stocks seeing biggest impact today even if you don't own them.
Tier 3 — General market news. Macro events, global developments, economy.

Push notifications fire only for Tier 1. Never for general news. No spam.

MODULE 7 — GLOBAL MORNING BRIEF
Every morning before Indian markets open at 9:15 AM, AEGIS sends a brief showing how global markets closed overnight — US markets, SGX Nifty, crude oil price, gold price, USD/INR exchange rate, and predicted impact on your specific portfolio for the day. Users stop opening five different apps every morning. Everything they need is in one place, personalised to their holdings.

MODULE 8 — FII/DII ACTIVITY TRACKER
Foreign Institutional Investors hold approximately 20–22% of all NSE-listed stocks. When they collectively sell, Indian markets fall regardless of fundamentals. When they buy, markets rise. Their daily activity is public data published by NSE and BSE every evening — but no retail app presents it connected to your personal holdings. AEGIS shows net FII and DII buying or selling every day, which sectors they moved in and out of, and maps it directly to your portfolio — telling you which of your stocks are in sectors seeing institutional inflows or outflows right now.

MODULE 9 — ECONOMIC CALENDAR
RBI monetary policy decisions, US Fed meetings, quarterly earnings results, Union Budget, monthly inflation data — these are the events that move markets. Most retail investors miss them or find out after the fact. AEGIS maintains a rolling 30-day calendar of all market-moving events, sends advance alerts for events affecting your specific holdings, and tells you what to expect and why it matters for your portfolio — before it happens.

