### WEALTH PLANNING

MODULE 14 — GOAL-BASED INVESTING
Instead of thinking about stocks, users think about their real life goals. Car in 3 years. House in 10 years. Child's education in 15 years. Retirement in 30 years. The user sets the goal and timeline. AEGIS reverse-engineers how much they need to invest every month to reach it. It tracks live progress with a visual progress bar. When markets move, it automatically recalculates and tells the user what changes. This changes the user's relationship with investing entirely — they stop panicking about daily price movements because they can see they are still on track for the thing that actually matters to them.

MODULE 15 — SIP AND MUTUAL FUND TRACKER
Most Indian investors have both direct stocks and SIPs or mutual funds managed in completely separate apps with no connection between them. AEGIS brings both together into one complete wealth picture. It shows total wealth across both, upcoming SIP dates and amounts, individual fund performance, and sector overlap detection. If your direct stocks are already 50% IT and your SIP is going into an IT-heavy fund, AEGIS flags it.

MODULE 16 — IPO TRACKER
Every upcoming IPO displayed with a simple AEGIS rating, the Grey Market Premium (informal indicator of expected listing gains), a one-line verdict in plain English, and a specific note on whether the IPO fits your portfolio based on your current sector exposure and risk profile. Direct link to apply through your connected broker.

MODULE 17 — TAX AND P&L SUMMARY
At any point in the year, AEGIS shows your complete capital gains picture — STCG and LTCG clearly separated, total tax liability calculated, and remaining exemption limit shown. Before March 31st every year, it automatically identifies tax loss harvesting opportunities — stocks where booking a loss would offset your gains and reduce your tax bill. At year end, a complete downloadable tax report is generated — ready to hand to your CA or use for filing directly.

